						<summary>

						<p>On a stone planted near a pickly-pear bush.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1088, Uttarāyaṇa Saṅkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to register a gift (some land) to the god Sōmanāthadēva by Nūki-śeṭṭi, for the merit of his parents.</p>						

						</summary>
